<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-13T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-13T20:00:00-05:00" n="1118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1118">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/221</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-13T20:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1916, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram January 25, 7 p.m. As stated Department’s January 21, 5
                            p.m., stock Compañia Petrolera Maritima owned by American citizens.
                            Statement of Foreign Secretary that interests Mexican citizens only
                            concerned is inaccurate and his reply unsatisfactory. It is important
                            that <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> Government state its views and
                            position on questions presented by this case.</p>
                        <p>Renew representations in behalf company.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>